<h3>Not Yet Another Reinvention Of The Wheel</h3>
<h3>Where WPDocs are Born</h3>
<p>There are a lot of great resources out there for learning about the web. Each page on WPD started out as a page on MSDN. Microsoft generously donated their content to get us started. MDN is a favorite among professional developers for looking up reference docs about the web. Mozilla has been generously allowing volunteers to copy content from MDN to WPD, helping us improve each page. And much of the content on WPD comes from the specifications themselves. Web standards specifications are written by experts to specify how browser makers should build their browsers. WPD will grow into the place for future spec writers to document their spec for developers. Easier for devs to understand and find the information their need.</p>
<p>Mashing together information from various sources takes time, however. Scripts have gotten us started, but then we need real people to write or rewrite each page to make it useful.</p>
